# Harness Guardrails

- Prefer local mocks and fixtures over real mailbox/calendar services during development.
- Run `npm run harness:semantic` after code edits and `npm run check:standard` before commits.
- Do not write `.env` files, force-push, or run destructive database commands without explicit user approval.
- Treat GET routes as read-only. Side effects belong in POST/PUT/PATCH/DELETE routes.
- Promote repeated failures from `.harness/error-journal.md` into `.harness/patterns-cache.json`.
- For code tasks, implement first, then run independent audit and fix all Critical/High findings before delivery.

